import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='cx', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(x=data['cx'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['cx'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(x=data['cx'].median(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['cx'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the cx field?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('cx')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    top_5_names = data['name'].value_counts().nlargest(5)
    sns.barplot(x=top_5_names.index, y=top_5_names.values)
    plt.title('What are the top 5 names in the name field?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Name')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
